        <detaileddescription>
<para>Copyright (c) 2023-2024 Analog Devices, Inc. All Rights Reserved. This software is proprietary to Analog Devices, Inc. and its licensors. A TMCL Tx/Rx format will always be lke the following:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Tx: | [[Module Address]] | &lt;Command&gt; | &lt;Type&gt; | &lt;Motor&gt; | </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>| </para>
<para>| </para>
<para>| </para>
<para>| [[Checksum]]<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Rx: | [[Reply Address]] | &lt;Module Address&gt; | &lt;Status&gt; | &lt;Command&gt; | </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>| </para>
<para>| </para>
<para>| </para>
<para>| [[Checksum]]</para>
<para>Specifically, for CAN interface:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Both Tx and Rx length will just be 7 bytes. Those enclosed with [[]] are not part of the message (they will automatically be added on the hardware-level).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Module Address: CAN-ID of the Sender</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Reply Address: CAN-ID of the Receiver</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Command, Type, <ref refid="classMotor" kindref="compound">Motor</ref>, Status can be either of the values enumerated below </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
